snippet: Republicans seized on the latest insurance enrollment numbers under the Affordable Care Act as evidence that the law would not work.
abstract: Obama administration officials say people signing up for health insurance through Affordable Care Act's marketplaces tend to be older and potentially less healthy; demographic mix could threaten law's underpinnings and cause premiums to rise in future; Republicans seize on enrollment numbers as evidence that law will not work.

byline.original: By MICHAEL D. SHEAR and ROBERT PEAR

lead_paragraph: Republicans seized on the latest insurance enrollment numbers under the Affordable Care Act as evidence that the law would not work.

headline.main: Older Pool of Health Care Enrollees Stirs Fears on Costs
headline.print_headline: Older People Lead Sign-Ups for Insurance
